GeneralComments:
24/7
Two reserved car parks and two charging stations. The first is an ABB fast charger with three tethered cables: CHAdeMO, CCS Combo (Type 1), and a Type 2 (43kW) AC. Adjacent to this is a second charging station with two Type 2 (22kW) socket outlets (which will require EV drivers to supply their own cable). The chargers operate 24/7 however a Charge.net.nz RFID is required for their use. There's WIFI across the road from the local library.

GeneralComments:
Normal camping fees apply for charging electric vehicles.
Kerr Bay campground is NOT a free charging site. It is a busy campground operating on a booking system during the summer. From mid-December to end of April everyone using the sites must book and pay the full rate online or at the Rotoiti/Nelson Lakes Visitor Centre. Normal camping fees apply for charging electric vehicles. From 1st May to mid-December vehicles using the powered sites for charging can do so 10am to 3pm for a donation payable at the Rotoiti/Nelson Lakes Visitor Centre. After 3pm the full camp fee must be paid as any vehicle charging is blocking the site from campers.

GeneralComments: Three EV charging points in the main car park for use by visitors to ZEALANDIA. Conversion lead for Mennekes available at admissions desk. We are a 225 hectare ecosanctuary with a cafe and exhibition so feel free to charge your car while you recharge yourself by immersing yourself in our native flora and fauna.  Parking is not reserved for EVs. Type 2 chargers are 3.5 kW.

GeneralComments:
24/7
The Portobello Village Tourist Park is ideally located to allow you to explore the (very hilly) Otago Peninsula. You might take a stroll down to the pub or cafes while your battery charges, or to climb Cone Hill for magnificent views up and down Otago Harbour. If you want a longer walk, tramp over to Hoopers and Papanui Inlet. With prior arrangement (ring 03 478 0359), we can have bicycles delivered for day or part day hire. Most of the plugs are Blue Commando (16 Amp) but one household 3-point plug (8 Amp) is also available by the BBQ area. Mel and Ralph welcome EV owners to Kaitangata. Their motor camp is just over the road from the Matau branch of Clutha River – you could catch brown trout and maybe even a salmon in the river, or just dip your toes while your car battery recharges. There are also lots of local walks, a swimming pool and a Museum nearby. A modest charge ($1 per hour) is levied for day visits, but this will be waived if you stay overnight in one of their cabins or tent sites.

Daylight hours only
Strath Taieri Hotel & Backpackers has a 16 Amp caravan styled plug just inside a set of double doors (it used to be used for a tanker’s pump). A standard 5-m longer charger lead will reach it from the roadside, but the need to have the doors open while charging precludes use of the charger at night (when that side of the hotel is locked). While charging you could visit many of Middlemarch’s cafes and eating places or their excellent Museum, or you can hire bikes for a zip down the Rail Trail. Strath Taieri Hotel & Backpackers even have a courtesy car that you can borrow (provided you show them your drivers’ license) to visit some of the local historical places, to take a walk up onto the Rock & Pillar Range, or visit Sutton Salt Lake (there is a superb walk around the lake and Department of Conservation Reserve).

$2/hour for charging; free if you are staying in one of their cabins, motel units or tent sites.
24/7
Moeraki Village Holiday Park has several 16 Amp caravan plugs available for daytime charging or charging overnight while you stay in their motel units, cabins or tent sites. You might like to take a 45 minute walk to the famous Mooeraki Boulders while you charge, or visit the local tavern or the well-known Fleurs restaurant,or walk over to the Kaik.

$2/h while charging; or $1/h if you are hiring one of our sites or units.
24/7
We have several 16Amp caravan plug sites available for your EV, irrespective of whether you are staying in one of our tent, cabins, tourist flats, studio units or motel units. You can take a bush walk around Ross Creek Reservour (just alongside our park)while you recharge, or 2-3 hour walk up The "Pineapple Track" to the hills overlooking Dunedin; or go and see the local glow worms if you are staying overnight.

GeneralComments:
Charging for the day only is $4 and if you are camping it is $6 for each night you stay
07 AM - 08 PM
We have 14 powered camping sites that has 16A power outlets that can be used for charging vehicles while staying camping or just passing for a cup of coffee or buying products in our small provision store. Charging for the day only is $4 and if you are camping it is $6 for each night you stay. We have amazing views over the islands and you are welcome to have a relaxing moment while adding power to continue your journey.

GeneralComments:
$10 for 3pin 10amp daytime charging and can use amenities (toilets, kitchen). Short term 3pin 10amp $2/hour if don't use amenities. 10amp charging park by Office (see photo of plugged in car). Powered campsite $20 for 24 hours 16 amp blue commando (stay the night; cost for unit is extra $25/person). EFTPOS available.
Come for casual daytime charging (go for a beautiful hike up colonial knob, entrance is just meters away) and Low cost accommodation (bring own bedding). 10-15 min walking distance to restaurants, shopping mall, aquatic centre, ten pin bowling, go karts, Pataka Museum, railway. Information at http://www.campelsdon.co.nz/phone/casual-bookings.html

GeneralComments:
If camp office is closed please pay at the pub which is open till late
There are a couple of Blue Commando sockets available for EV charging just past the office and several more around the camp. Negotiable, eg $5 for a charge.
On main highway, just a few meters before cafès and shops. Convenient location. Manager is "Colin" and he is happy for responsible car owners to recharge at his park. A plug adapter to alter the blue commando berths into a small 3-point plug (i.e. 10 amp S3112; this is not the larger earth S3112 15amp plug) is only available if you ring up and arrange prior to visiting.
